    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[Er81h] Erd\\H{o}s, P., Some problems and results on additive and multiplicative\nnumber theory. Analytic number theory (Philadelphia, Pa., 1980) (1981), 171-182.\n \n [ErHa78] Erd\\H{o}s, P. and Hall, R. R., On some unconventional problems on the divisors of integers. J. Austral. Math. Soc. Ser. A (1978), 479--485.",
      "remarks": "The function $\\tau_\\perp(n)$ was considered by Erd\\H{o}s and Hall \\cite{ErHa78}. It is trivial that $\\tau_\\perp(n)\\geq \\omega(n)$ (with equality for infinitely many $n$). Erd\\H{o}s and Hall prove, for all $\\epsilon>0$ and sufficiently large $x$,\\[\\max_{n<x} \\tau_\\perp(n) > \\exp((\\log\\log x)^{2-\\epsilon}).\\]Erd\\H{o}s and Simonovits (see \\cite{Er81h}) proved\\[(2^{1/2}+o(1))^k < g(k) < (2-c)^k\\]for some constant $c>0$."
    },
